The paper deals with flow rate allocation in wireless multi-hop networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and communication systems. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also involves optimization problems and mathematical modeling, which are relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The use of distributed algorithms and simulations suggests a possible fit with cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
